=\"https://www.vlaamswoningfonds.be/onze-diensten/verzekering-gewaarborgd-wonen\">the website of the</a> Flemish Housing Fund.</p><p>Please note: your application must be made within one year of the first or only capital drawdown of the loan.</p><ul><li>You must make the application <strong>within </strong>one year of the first or only capital drawdown of your loan.</li><li>You will receive an acknowledgement of receipt from the Flemish Housing Fund.</li><li>The Flemish Housing Fund will check whether your application is complete and contains all the necessary documents. If this is not the case, they will ask you by e-mail (or by letter if you explicitly request it) for the missing documents.</li><li>Once your file is complete, a decision will follow within 90 days.</li></ul><p>If you are admitted to the insurance, you will be insured for 10 years from the date the Flemish Housing Fund received your application. You will be sent a policy by the insurer. It explains what you must do if you become involuntarily unemployed or disabled. So keep this document carefully.</p><h3>Intervention</h3><p>If you are insured and you fall out of work, you can apply for an allowance:</p><ul><li>A <strong>waiting period of 3 months</strong> applies from the time you apply. You can only get a loan repayment allowance if you can prove that you have been continuously disabled or involuntarily and fully unemployed for at least 3 months.</li><li>The relief does not work retrospectively. So you will not get a concession for the waiting period.</li></ul><p>All the information to apply for a <strong>relief</strong> can be found in the insurance policy you received from Ethias. You can also contact Ethias.</p><h3>Refinancing</h3><p>If you <strong>refinance</strong>, the insurance you already had will continue as normal. You do not have to do anything.</p><p>If you had not yet applied for guaranteed living insurance for your loan, you can no longer get it when you refinance that loan either.</